<%# /otp-vs-ninety-eos-one -- v7 (light, editorial). Bottom-funnel comparison
    page. Rule: do NOT out-checkbox the incumbents on Stage-1 EOS features (we
    lose that). Concede two rows honestly, then dominate every row about agents
    + the pricing flip (humans free / agents paid), where they are structurally
    N/A. Single primary CTA -> /sign-up. Tone: confident, not insulting; the
    table does the hitting. %>
<style>
  .cmp-wrap { overflow-x:auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch; }
  .cmp { width:100%; border-collapse:separate; border-spacing:0; min-width:640px; font-size:15px; }
  .cmp th, .cmp td { padding:14px 16px; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid var(--line,#e6e8ec); vertical-align:middle; }
  .cmp th { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk','Inter',sans-serif; font-weight:800; font-size:14px; }
  .cmp td:first-child, .cmp th:first-child { text-align:left; color:var(--ink-soft,#494d57); font-weight:600; }
  .cmp .col-otp { background:rgba(255,122,26,0.06); border-left:2px solid var(--orange,#ff7a1a); border-right:2px solid var(--orange,#ff7a1a); }
  .cmp thead .col-otp { border-top:2px solid var(--orange,#ff7a1a); border-top-left-radius:12px; border-top-right-radius:12px; color:var(--orange-deep,#d65a00); }
  .cmp tr:last-child .col-otp { border-bottom:2px solid var(--orange,#ff7a1a); }
  .cmp .yes { color:var(--orange-deep,#d65a00); font-weight:800; }
  .cmp .no  { color:#c2c6cd; font-weight:700; }
  .cmp .price { font-family:'Schibsted Grotesk','Inter',sans-serif; font-weight:800; color:var(--ink,#14161c); }
  .cmp .free { color:var(--orange-deep,#d65a00); font-weight:800; }
  .cmp .muted { color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); font-size:13px; }
  .cmp-note { font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute,#888c96); margin-top:14px; line-height:1.6; }
  .stack { display:grid; gap:0; }
</style>

<!-- ================= HERO ================= -->
<section class="bg-[var(--white)]">
  <div class="max-w-[1080px] mx-auto px-6 pt-[120px] pb-12 sm:pt-[140px] sm:pb-16 text-center">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-4 flex items-center gap-2.5 justify-center">
      <span class="tick" style="background:var(--orange);"></span>OTP vs Ninety vs EOS One
    </div>
    <h1 class="font-display text-[var(--ink)] mx-auto max-w-[20ch]"
        style="font-size:clamp(2.2rem,4.6vw,3.7rem); line-height:1.05; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.025em;">
      Ninety and EOS One run your EOS. <span class="text-[var(--orange-deep)]">OTP lets you hire agents into it.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-[17px] sm:text-[18px] text-[var(--ink-soft)] leading-[1.6] max-w-[40rem] mx-auto mt-5">
      They're good EOS&reg; software &mdash; they digitize the system you already run. OTP runs the same system, and lets AI agents take real seats next to your people, with real numbers to hit and real work to do. Your whole team is free. You only pay for the agents.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 justify-center mt-8">
      <a href="/sign-up" class="btn-primary px-8 py-4 text-[16px]">Start free &mdash; no card &rarr;</a>
      <a href="#pricing" class="btn-ghost px-8 py-4 text-[16px]">See the difference</a>
    </div>
    <p class="eyebrow mt-7 justify-center flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
      <span>Whole team free</span><span style="color:var(--ink-mute);">&middot;</span>
      <span style="color:var(--orange-deep);">Agents do the work</span><span style="color:var(--ink-mute);">&middot;</span>
      <span style="color:var(--blue-deep);">Built on the EOS you run</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= THE PRICING WEAPON ================= -->
<section id="pricing" class="bg-[var(--grey)]">
  <div class="max-w-[920px] mx-auto px-6 py-18 sm:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-[640px] mb-10">
      <div class="eyebrow mb-4">The difference, in two seconds</div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-[var(--ink)] tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.1]" style="font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.4vw,2.6rem); font-weight:700;">
        Everyone gives the first user away. Only OTP gives your whole team away.
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-wrap rounded-[14px] bg-[var(--white)]" style="box-shadow:0 1px 0 rgba(20,22,28,.04), 0 18px 40px rgba(20,22,28,.06);">
      <table class="cmp">
        <thead>
          <tr><th></th><th>Ninety</th><th>EOS One</th><th class="col-otp">OTP</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>First user</td><td>Free</td><td>Free</td><td class="col-otp free">Free</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Every other user</td><td class="price">$11<span class="muted">/mo each</span></td><td class="price">$10<span class="muted">/mo each</span></td><td class="col-otp free">Free</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AI agents that do the work</td><td class="muted">Not available</td><td class="muted">Not available</td><td class="col-otp price">$11<span class="muted">/mo per agent*</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="cmp-note max-w-[640px]">
      You used to pay $11 for one more human seat. On OTP your people are free, and $11 buys an agent that works around the clock and never forgets a thing. <span class="muted">*Founding price. Per active agent seat. Humans always free.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= WHAT NONE OF THEM CAN DO ================= -->
<section class="bg-[var(--white)]">
  <div class="max-w-[920px] mx-auto px-6 py-18 sm:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-[640px] mb-10">
      <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Where the comparison ends</div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-[var(--ink)] tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.1]" style="font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.4vw,2.6rem); font-weight:700;">
        They added an AI assistant. OTP gives you AI employees.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[16px] text-[var(--ink-soft)] leading-[1.65] mt-5">
        EOS One has Atlas. Ninety has a Rock companion. They answer questions about your business. OTP's agents <em>are</em> the business &mdash; they take a seat, own a number, and do the work between meetings. Here's where the two paths split.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-wrap rounded-[14px] bg-[var(--white)]" style="box-shadow:0 1px 0 rgba(20,22,28,.04), 0 18px 40px rgba(20,22,28,.06);">
      <table class="cmp">
        <thead>
          <tr><th></th><th>Ninety</th><th>EOS One</th><th class="col-otp">OTP</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Full EOS toolset (chart, scorecard, priorities, weekly meeting)</td><td class="yes">&#10003;</td><td class="yes">&#10003;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>The <em>official</em> EOS product</td><td class="no">&mdash;</td><td class="yes">&#10003;</td><td class="col-otp no">&mdash;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AI in the product</td><td class="muted">Assistant</td><td class="muted">Assistant (Atlas)</td><td class="col-otp" style="color:var(--orange-deep);font-weight:800;">Employees</td></tr>
          <tr><td>An AI agent can hold a seat on your chart</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Agents carry their own KPIs on the scorecard</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Agents do work <em>between</em> meetings</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>An agent that runs your weekly meeting</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003; <span class="muted">Dan</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Your whole team, free</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Your company learns from every other company on it</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A working agent the day you sign up</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="no">&#10007;</td><td class="col-otp yes">&#10003; <span class="muted">Dan</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="cmp-note max-w-[640px]">Yes &mdash; they're real, polished, established EOS software, and EOS One is the official one. We'll give them that. Everything below those two rows, their data model can't do: it assumes every seat is a human, and they charge you per human.</p>
  </div>
</section>

